    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Tail light removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000967",
          "label": "Tail light removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Valve removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "962_3.0_jpn_11392918_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The brake/tail light is an integral part of the tail light assy. and cannot be detached by itself. Therefore, if the brake/tail light is to be detached, Remove the tail light.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000967",
          "label": "Remove the tail light.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Rotate the socket (A) counterclockwise to remove it. Remove the valve (B). Brake/Tail light: LED (non-disassembled (tail light assy. one piece)) Rear turn signal light: 12V-21W Backlight: 12V-16W"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    }
